dt: {bc}a shelter or repair shop for automotive vehicles
{bc}a cabinet with a vertical rolling door that is used for storing a small kitchen appliance

et: borrowed from French, "docking (of a boat), place to store vehicles," from {it}garer{/it} "to dock, moor" (going back to Middle French {it}guerrer, garrer{/it} "to moor (a boat), shelter (merchandise)," going back to Old French (Brittany) {it}varer{/it} "to protect oneself against," probably borrowed from Old Norse {it}vara{/it} "to warn," {it}varask{/it} "to be on one's guard") + {it}-age{/it} {et_link|-age|-age} {ma}{mat|ware:3|}{/ma}
shortdef: a shelter or repair shop for automotive vehicles
a cabinet with a vertical rolling door that is used for storing a small kitchen appliance
to keep or put in a garage
